title: Enums for Level 1 feed System message types. See Level 1 Port System Messages

javaEnums.title: Result of sending the S,KEY,##### message back to IQFeed.
A notification that the symbol limit has been reached including the symbol which was not not serviced.
This message is received after your program connects to IQConnect. It indicates the IP addresses that IQFeed is to use to connect to the data sources.
This message is received after your program connects to IQConnect. It contains customer information.
This message is sent in response to a S,REQUEST STATS<LF> message.
This message is sent in response to a S,REQUEST FUNDAMENTAL FIELDNAMES<LF> message. The message is a comma delimited list of all Level1 field names for Fundamental messages.
This message is sent in response to a S,REQUEST ALL UPDATE FIELDNAMES<LF> message. The message is a comma delimited list of all available Level1 field names for Update and Summary messages.

This message is sent in response to a S,REQUEST CURRENT UPDATE FIELDNAMES<LF> message. The message is a comma delimited list of the Level1 field names currently selected for Update and Summary messages.
This message is sent in response to a S,SET LOG LEVELS<LF> message. The message is a comma delimited list of the logging levels currently selected for IQConnect.
This message is sent in reponse to a S,REQUEST WATCHES<LF> message. The message is a comma delimited list of all Level1 symbols that are currently being watched.
